---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Terms of Use | Sight Words"
  description="Read the terms of use for this free educational sight word website."
  canonicalUrl="https://placeholder.com/terms-of-use"
>
  <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Terms of Use</h1>

  <p class="text-gray-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
    These Terms of Use explain the basic rules for using this website. By using the site, you agree to these terms.
  </p>

  <section class="space-y-6 text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Educational Use and “As Is” Service</h2>
      <p>
        This website is provided for general educational purposes only. Content is offered “as is” without promises
        that the site will always be available, error-free, or perfect for every learner.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">No Guarantees</h2>
      <p>
        We do not guarantee specific learning results, reading outcomes, or accuracy in every situation. Teaching and
        learning progress can vary from child to child.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Your Responsibility</h2>
      <p>
        You are responsible for how you use the content and tools on this site. Parents, teachers, and caregivers
        should decide what is appropriate for their own students and children.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Personal and Educational Use</h2>
      <p>
        Site content is intended for personal, classroom, and other educational use. Please do not misuse the site,
        copy it in a harmful way, or use it for unlawful purposes.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Limitation of Liability</h2>
      <p>
        To the fullest extent allowed by law, we are not liable for any loss, damage, or issues that may result from
        using this site or relying on its content.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div>
      <h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Changes to the Site and Terms</h2>
      <p>
        We may update, change, or remove parts of the site at any time. We may also update these Terms of Use, and
        the newest version posted on this page will apply.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
